<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="435" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,798,1726]" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,798,825]" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1907" box="[406,507,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Eleazara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[406,507,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Eleazara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1803" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1803" box="[661,916,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Ledra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[661,728,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Ledra</emphasis>
Fabricius, 1803
</taxonomicName>
. It can be distinguished from the latter by: 1) pronotum longer than crown, with the lateral dilated areas laminately subangular (
<figureCitation box="[1090,1191,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1810,1835]" captionTargetBox="[182,1411,221,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,170,1757]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Eleazara viraktamathi sp. nov. Holotype: 1. habitus, dorsal view; 2. habitus, lateral view; 3. habitus, ventral view; 4. pronotum, dorsal view; 5. face, anterior view; 6. head, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615517/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Figs. 1, 4</figureCitation>
); 2) scutellum with a sagittal elevated crest-like process (
<figureCitation box="[549,646,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1810,1835]" captionTargetBox="[182,1411,221,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,170,1757]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Eleazara viraktamathi sp. nov. Holotype: 1. habitus, dorsal view; 2. habitus, lateral view; 3. habitus, ventral view; 4. pronotum, dorsal view; 5. face, anterior view; 6. head, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615517/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Figs. 1, 2</figureCitation>
); 3) the long metathoracic tarsomere I (
<figureCitation box="[1091,1153,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1810,1835]" captionTargetBox="[182,1411,221,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,170,1757]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Eleazara viraktamathi sp. nov. Holotype: 1. habitus, dorsal view; 2. habitus, lateral view; 3. habitus, ventral view; 4. pronotum, dorsal view; 5. face, anterior view; 6. head, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615517/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); and 4) dorsum strongly granulose (
<figureCitation box="[275,383,907,934]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1810,1835]" captionTargetBox="[182,1411,221,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,170,1757]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Eleazara viraktamathi sp. nov. Holotype: 1. habitus, dorsal view; 2. habitus, lateral view; 3. habitus, ventral view; 4. pronotum, dorsal view; 5. face, anterior view; 6. head, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615517/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Figs. 1–6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="435" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,798,1726]" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,942,969]" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Description.</emphasis>
Body medium to rather large (10.9–17.3mm). Dorsum densely punctate. Head broad, shorter and narrower than pronotum, longer than the width of the anterior margin of the scutellum. Crown foliaceous, punctate, nodulate, not rugose, slightly convex, produced forward, anterior margin angulate, straight in front of eyes and then oblique to apex, median length much greater than width between eyes (
<figureCitation box="[967,1095,1050,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1810,1835]" captionTargetBox="[182,1411,221,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,170,1757]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Eleazara viraktamathi sp. nov. Holotype: 1. habitus, dorsal view; 2. habitus, lateral view; 3. habitus, ventral view; 4. pronotum, dorsal view; 5. face, anterior view; 6. head, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615517/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Figs. 1, 2, 5</figureCitation>
). Coronal suture complete and distinct (
<figureCitation box="[241,336,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1810,1835]" captionTargetBox="[182,1411,221,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,170,1757]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Eleazara viraktamathi sp. nov. Holotype: 1. habitus, dorsal view; 2. habitus, lateral view; 3. habitus, ventral view; 4. pronotum, dorsal view; 5. face, anterior view; 6. head, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615517/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Figs. 1, 6</figureCitation>
). Ocelli well-developed, near posterior margin of crown, approximately as close to each other as to eyes (
<figureCitation box="[215,311,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1810,1835]" captionTargetBox="[182,1411,221,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,170,1757]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Eleazara viraktamathi sp. nov. Holotype: 1. habitus, dorsal view; 2. habitus, lateral view; 3. habitus, ventral view; 4. pronotum, dorsal view; 5. face, anterior view; 6. head, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615517/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Figs. 1, 6</figureCitation>
). Face elongate, broadest between eyes. Proepisternum large and collar-like (
<figureCitation box="[1171,1239,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1810,1835]" captionTargetBox="[182,1411,221,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,170,1757]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Eleazara viraktamathi sp. nov. Holotype: 1. habitus, dorsal view; 2. habitus, lateral view; 3. habitus, ventral view; 4. pronotum, dorsal view; 5. face, anterior view; 6. head, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615517/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Pronotum broad, with paired sublateral longitudinal rows of tubercles and paired submedial carinae variably developed, strongly granulose on posterior area, anterior margin straight or slightly convex, posterior margin slightly or moderately concave (
<figureCitation box="[1321,1421,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1810,1835]" captionTargetBox="[182,1411,221,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,170,1757]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Eleazara viraktamathi sp. nov. Holotype: 1. habitus, dorsal view; 2. habitus, lateral view; 3. habitus, ventral view; 4. pronotum, dorsal view; 5. face, anterior view; 6. head, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615517/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Figs. 1–4</figureCitation>
). Scutellum and exposed part of mesonotum triangular, shorter than pronotum, with sagittal elevated crest. Scutellar suture distinct, reaching lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[504,605,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1810,1835]" captionTargetBox="[182,1411,221,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,170,1757]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Eleazara viraktamathi sp. nov. Holotype: 1. habitus, dorsal view; 2. habitus, lateral view; 3. habitus, ventral view; 4. pronotum, dorsal view; 5. face, anterior view; 6. head, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615517/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Figs. 1, 2</figureCitation>
). Forewing granulose, venation reticulate, especially apically, veins elevated and prominent; appendix poorly developed (
<figureCitation box="[633,733,1303,1330]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1810,1835]" captionTargetBox="[182,1411,221,1680]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,170,1757]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Eleazara viraktamathi sp. nov. Holotype: 1. habitus, dorsal view; 2. habitus, lateral view; 3. habitus, ventral view; 4. pronotum, dorsal view; 5. face, anterior view; 6. head, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615517/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Figs. 1, 2</figureCitation>
). Hind wings hyaline, fully-developed. Pro- and mesothoracic leg chaetotaxy reduced, with setae short and fine. Legs of moderate length. Hind femur macrosetal formula 2 + 0; hind tibiae dilated, with 5 to 6 stout and enlarged setae rows perpendicular to axis of leg anterodorsally (AD); posterodorsal (PD) setae short and fine; anteroventral (AV) and posteroventral (PV) setae shorter and finer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,798,1726]" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">
Male 8th sternite about as long as or longer than 7th sternite, posterior margin moderately concave medially, with or without numerous short setae apically on ventral surface (Fig. 15). Male pygofer almost triangular, without terminal process; ventroposterior margin with terminally directed process (
<figureCitation box="[753,853,1519,1546]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,818,843]" captionTargetBox="[192,1344,207,675]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,151,763]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–8. Eleazara viraktamathi sp. nov. 7. male genital capsule, dorsal view; 8. male genital capsule, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615521/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Figs. 7, 8</figureCitation>
, 12, 14). Subgenital plate ligulate and depressed, fused at base, tapered to rounded apex, with numerous short setae on ventral surface (
<figureCitation box="[993,1093,1555,1582]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,818,843]" captionTargetBox="[192,1344,207,675]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,151,763]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–8. Eleazara viraktamathi sp. nov. 7. male genital capsule, dorsal view; 8. male genital capsule, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615521/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Figs. 7, 8</figureCitation>
, 12, 13). Aedeagal shaft tubular, curved dorsad, with (
<taxonomicName authority="Cai &amp; He" authorityName="Cai &amp; He" authorityYear="1997" box="[374,661,1591,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Eleazara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yangi">
<emphasis box="[374,545,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Eleazara yangi</emphasis>
Cai &amp; He
</taxonomicName>
) or without (
<taxonomicName authority="Huang &amp; Zhang" authorityName="Huang &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2018" box="[799,1215,1591,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Eleazara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viraktamathi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[799,1035,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Eleazara viraktamathi</emphasis>
Huang &amp; Zhang
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1221,1305,1591,1617]" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1221,1305,1591,1617]" pageId="1" pageNumber="435" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
) paired processes arising subapically (
<figureCitation box="[437,510,1627,1654]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,818,843]" captionTargetBox="[192,1344,207,675]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,151,763]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–8. Eleazara viraktamathi sp. nov. 7. male genital capsule, dorsal view; 8. male genital capsule, lateral view. Scale bars = 0.5mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615521/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="435">Figs. 7</figureCitation>
–10, 12). Style slender or broad, curved ventrally at apex (Figs. 9, 10). Connective short, T-shaped or trapeziform (Figs. 9–11).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
